records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which charges child enticement, contrary to Section 948.02 of the Wisconsin Statutes.
GUILTY plea entered to the charge in the Amended Information.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for seven (7) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Undergo a psycho-sexual evaluation if the agent deems it appropriate;
3) Undergo sex offender treatment;
4) Comply with the sex offender registry;
5) No contact with the victim, the victims family and siblings;
6) No contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent or unless supervised by an adult approved by DOC;
7) No possession or use of the internet or any internet enabled devices;
8) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
9) Pay court costs;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
11) spend one (1) year in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
Minutes.
